Exercise 1: Spring Web Project Setup
📄 Description:
Create a basic Spring Boot project using Maven that exposes a simple REST API using Spring Web.

📥 Sample Input (URL):
http://localhost:8080/hello

📤 Sample Output (Response):
Hello from Spring Boot!

🛠️ What is Used to Bring this Output:

Spring Boot Starter Web (dependency for REST APIs)

Main Class (SpringRestHandsonApplication.java) to launch the Spring Boot app

Controller Class (HelloController.java) to define the /hello endpoint

Embedded Tomcat Server started automatically by Spring Boot on port 8080
